---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Features"
  description="Explore the Donjon Platform's 17 security scanners, 30 compliance frameworks, AI-powered analysis engine, FAIR risk quantification, and flexible deployment options."
>
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="bg-navy-950 py-16 sm:py-24">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="text-center">
        <h1 class="text-4xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-white sm:text-5xl lg:text-6xl">
          Platform Features
        </h1>
        <p class="mx-auto mt-6 max-w-3xl text-lg text-slate-400">
          A comprehensive security assessment platform that replaces $110K+/yr in commercial tooling. 17 scanners, 30 compliance frameworks, AI-powered analysis, and FAIR risk quantification -- all in a single deployable package.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- 17 Security Scanners -->
  <section class="bg-navy-900 py-16 sm:py-20">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white sm:text-4xl">17 Security Scanners</h2>
        <p class="mt-4 max-w-3xl text-slate-400">
          Purpose-built scanners covering every layer of your infrastructure. Each scanner produces structured findings that feed directly into compliance mapping, AI analysis, and FAIR risk quantification.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 gap-6 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3">
        <!-- Scanner Cards -->
        <div class="rounded-lg border border-navy-700 bg-navy-800 p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-cyan-400">Network Scanner</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-400">TCP/UDP port scanning, service detection, and network topology mapping across IPv4 and IPv6 targets.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-lg border border-navy-700 bg-navy-800 p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-cyan-400">Vulnerability Scanner</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-400">CVE-based vulnerability identification with NVD correlation, EPSS scoring, and KEV catalog integration.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-lg border border-navy-700 bg-navy-800 p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-cyan-400">Web Application Scanner</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-400">OWASP Top 10 coverage including XSS, SQLi, CSRF, SSRF, and insecure deserialization detection.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-lg border border-navy-700 bg-navy-800 p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-cyan-400">SSL/TLS Scanner</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-400">Certificate validation, protocol version analysis, cipher suite grading, and expired certificate detection.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-lg border border-navy-700 bg-navy-800 p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-cyan-400">Windows Scanner</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-400">Windows host hardening assessment including patch status, local policy audit, and service configuration review.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-lg border border-navy-700 bg-navy-800 p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-cyan-400">Linux Scanner</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-400">Linux host security assessment covering CIS benchmarks, kernel parameters, file permissions, and package auditing.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-lg border border-navy-700 bg-navy-800 p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-cyan-400">Active Directory Scanner</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-400">AD enumeration and security assessment including Kerberoasting, delegation abuse, GPO analysis, and privilege escalation paths.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-lg border border-navy-700 bg-navy-800 p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-cyan-400">Cloud Scanner -- AWS</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-400">AWS security posture assessment covering IAM, S3, EC2, RDS, Lambda, and CloudTrail configuration review.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-lg border border-navy-700 bg-navy-800 p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-cyan-400">Cloud Scanner -- Azure</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-400">Azure security assessment including Entra ID, storage accounts, NSGs, Key Vault, and resource group policies.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-lg border border-navy-700 bg-navy-800 p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-cyan-400">Cloud Scanner -- GCP</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-400">Google Cloud security review covering IAM, GCS buckets, Compute Engine, VPC firewall rules, and Cloud KMS.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-lg border border-navy-700 bg-navy-800 p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-cyan-400">Container Scanner</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-400">Docker and Kubernetes security analysis including image vulnerability scanning, misconfigurations, and runtime policy review.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-lg border border-navy-700 bg-navy-800 p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-cyan-400">SBOM Scanner</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-400">Software Bill of Materials generation and analysis with dependency vulnerability mapping and license compliance checks.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-lg border border-navy-700 bg-navy-800 p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-cyan-400">Compliance Scanner</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-400">Automated control testing against 30 frameworks with evidence collection and gap analysis reporting.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-lg border border-navy-700 bg-navy-800 p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-cyan-400">Credential Audit Scanner</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-400">Password policy assessment, default credential detection, and leaked credential cross-referencing against known breach datasets.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-lg border border-navy-700 bg-navy-800 p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-cyan-400">ASM Scanner</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-400">Attack Surface Management with external asset discovery, subdomain enumeration, and exposed service identification.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-lg border border-navy-700 bg-navy-800 p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-cyan-400">OpenVAS Integration</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-400">Native OpenVAS/GVM integration for deep vulnerability assessment with automated scan orchestration and result ingestion.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-lg border border-navy-700 bg-navy-800 p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-cyan-400">Malware / YARA Scanner</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-400">YARA rule-based malware detection with custom rule support, IOC matching, and file integrity verification.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-lg border border-navy-700 bg-navy-800 p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-cyan-400">Shadow AI Discovery</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-400">Detect unauthorized AI/ML model usage, unsanctioned LLM API calls, and shadow AI deployments across your environment.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-lg border border-navy-700 bg-navy-800 p-6 sm:col-span-2 lg:col-span-3 border-cyan-600/30">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-cyan-400">Full-Suite Orchestrator</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-400">Unified orchestration layer that coordinates all 17 scanners into a single assessment workflow. Manages scan scheduling, parallel execution, result aggregation, and cross-scanner correlation for comprehensive security posture analysis.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- 30 Compliance Frameworks -->
  <section class="bg-navy-950 py-16 sm:py-20">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white sm:text-4xl">30 Compliance Frameworks</h2>
        <p class="mt-4 max-w-3xl text-slate-400">
          Automated control mapping and evidence collection across 30 industry and regulatory compliance frameworks. Scan results automatically map to applicable controls with gap analysis and remediation guidance.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 gap-8 lg:grid-cols-2">
        <!-- Primary Frameworks -->
        <div class="rounded-lg border border-navy-700 bg-navy-900 p-8">
          <h3 class="mb-6 text-xl font-semibold text-white">Featured Frameworks</h3>
          <div class="space-y-4">
            <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="mt-0.5 inline-block h-2 w-2 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-cyan-400"></span>
              <div>
                <p class="font-medium text-slate-200">NIST 800-53 Rev. 5</p>
                <p class="text-sm text-slate-400">Security and privacy controls for federal information systems and organizations.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="mt-0.5 inline-block h-2 w-2 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-cyan-400"></span>
              <div>
                <p class="font-medium text-slate-200">NIST CSF 2.0</p>
                <p class="text-sm text-slate-400">Cybersecurity Framework with Govern, Identify, Protect, Detect, Respond, and Recover functions.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="mt-0.5 inline-block h-2 w-2 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-cyan-400"></span>
              <div>
                <p class="font-medium text-slate-200">HIPAA</p>
                <p class="text-sm text-slate-400">Health Insurance Portability and Accountability Act security and privacy requirements.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="mt-0.5 inline-block h-2 w-2 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-cyan-400"></span>
              <div>
                <p class="font-medium text-slate-200">PCI-DSS v4.0</p>
                <p class="text-sm text-slate-400">Payment Card Industry Data Security Standard for cardholder data protection.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="mt-0.5 inline-block h-2 w-2 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-cyan-400"></span>
              <div>
                <p class="font-medium text-slate-200">ISO 27001:2022</p>
                <p class="text-sm text-slate-400">International standard for information security management systems (ISMS).</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="mt-0.5 inline-block h-2 w-2 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-cyan-400"></span>
              <div>
                <p class="font-medium text-slate-200">SOC 1 / SOC 2 Type II</p>
                <p class="text-sm text-slate-400">Service Organization Control reports for trust services criteria: security, availability, processing integrity, confidentiality, and privacy.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="mt-0.5 inline-block h-2 w-2 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-cyan-400"></span>
              <div>
                <p class="font-medium text-slate-200">CMMC</p>
                <p class="text-sm text-slate-400">Cybersecurity Maturity Model Certification for the defense industrial base.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-lg border border-navy-700 bg-navy-900 p-8">
          <h3 class="mb-6 text-xl font-semibold text-white">Additional Frameworks</h3>
          <div class="space-y-4">
            <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="mt-0.5 inline-block h-2 w-2 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-cyan-400"></span>
              <div>
                <p class="font-medium text-slate-200">FedRAMP</p>
                <p class="text-sm text-slate-400">Federal Risk and Authorization Management Program for cloud service providers.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="mt-0.5 inline-block h-2 w-2 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-cyan-400"></span>
              <div>
                <p class="font-medium text-slate-200">GDPR</p>
                <p class="text-sm text-slate-400">EU General Data Protection Regulation technical and organizational controls.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="mt-0.5 inline-block h-2 w-2 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-cyan-400"></span>
              <div>
                <p class="font-medium text-slate-200">SOX</p>
                <p class="text-sm text-slate-400">Sarbanes-Oxley Act IT general controls and financial reporting integrity.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="mt-0.5 inline-block h-2 w-2 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-cyan-400"></span>
              <div>
                <p class="font-medium text-slate-200">HITRUST CSF</p>
                <p class="text-sm text-slate-400">Common Security Framework integrating multiple standards for healthcare organizations.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="mt-0.5 inline-block h-2 w-2 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-cyan-400"></span>
              <div>
                <p class="font-medium text-slate-200">DORA</p>
                <p class="text-sm text-slate-400">Digital Operational Resilience Act for EU financial entities.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="mt-0.5 inline-block h-2 w-2 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-cyan-400"></span>
              <div>
                <p class="font-medium text-slate-200">NIS2</p>
                <p class="text-sm text-slate-400">EU Network and Information Security Directive for essential and important entities.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="mt-0.5 inline-block h-2 w-2 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-cyan-400"></span>
              <div>
                <p class="font-medium text-slate-200">EU AI Act</p>
                <p class="text-sm text-slate-400">European Union Artificial Intelligence Act compliance controls for AI system risk assessment.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="mt-8 text-sm text-slate-500">
        Plus 16 additional frameworks including CIS Controls v8, NERC CIP, SWIFT CSP, FFIEC, GLBA, FERPA, CCPA/CPRA, CJIS, ITAR, FISMA, COBIT 2019, CSA STAR, and more. Community Edition includes up to 3 frameworks.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- AI Engine -->
  <section class="bg-navy-900 py-16 sm:py-20">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white sm:text-4xl">AI Analysis Engine</h2>
        <p class="mt-4 max-w-3xl text-slate-400">
          Six-provider fallback architecture ensures AI-powered analysis is always available, from fully air-gapped local inference to cloud-based models. The engine automatically cascades through providers based on availability and configuration.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 gap-6 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3">
        <div class="rounded-lg border border-navy-700 bg-navy-800 p-6">
          <div class="mb-3 flex items-center gap-2">
            <span class="inline-flex h-8 w-8 items-center justify-center rounded-md bg-cyan-600/20 text-sm font-bold text-cyan-400">1</span>
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white">Ollama (Local)</h3>
          </div>
          <p class="text-sm text-slate-400">Local LLM inference via Ollama. Fully air-gapped operation with no data leaving your network. Supports Llama, Mistral, CodeLlama, and other open models.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-lg border border-navy-700 bg-navy-800 p-6">
          <div class="mb-3 flex items-center gap-2">
            <span class="inline-flex h-8 w-8 items-center justify-center rounded-md bg-cyan-600/20 text-sm font-bold text-cyan-400">2</span>
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white">StepFun</h3>
          </div>
          <p class="text-sm text-slate-400">StepFun API integration for cost-effective analysis with strong multilingual capabilities and competitive pricing.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-lg border border-navy-700 bg-navy-800 p-6">
          <div class="mb-3 flex items-center gap-2">
            <span class="inline-flex h-8 w-8 items-center justify-center rounded-md bg-cyan-600/20 text-sm font-bold text-cyan-400">3</span>
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white">Anthropic Claude</h3>
          </div>
          <p class="text-sm text-slate-400">Anthropic Claude integration for nuanced security analysis with strong reasoning capabilities and detailed remediation guidance.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-lg border border-navy-700 bg-navy-800 p-6">
          <div class="mb-3 flex items-center gap-2">
            <span class="inline-flex h-8 w-8 items-center justify-center rounded-md bg-cyan-600/20 text-sm font-bold text-cyan-400">4</span>
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white">Google Gemini</h3>
          </div>
          <p class="text-sm text-slate-400">Google Gemini for large-context analysis, capable of processing extensive scan result sets in a single pass.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-lg border border-navy-700 bg-navy-800 p-6">
          <div class="mb-3 flex items-center gap-2">
            <span class="inline-flex h-8 w-8 items-center justify-center rounded-md bg-cyan-600/20 text-sm font-bold text-cyan-400">5</span>
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white">OpenAI</h3>
          </div>
          <p class="text-sm text-slate-400">OpenAI integration for industry-standard AI analysis with broad security knowledge and structured output generation.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-lg border border-navy-700 bg-navy-800 p-6">
          <div class="mb-3 flex items-center gap-2">
            <span class="inline-flex h-8 w-8 items-center justify-center rounded-md bg-cyan-600/20 text-sm font-bold text-cyan-400">6</span>
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white">Pure-Python Template</h3>
          </div>
          <p class="text-sm text-slate-400">Zero-dependency fallback using rule-based Python templates. Ensures analysis output is always generated, even without any AI provider configured.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FAIR Risk Quantification -->
  <section class="bg-navy-950 py-16 sm:py-20">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="lg:grid lg:grid-cols-2 lg:gap-12 lg:items-start">
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white sm:text-4xl">FAIR Risk Quantification</h2>
          <p class="mt-4 text-slate-400">
            Translate technical vulnerabilities into dollar-quantified business risk using the Factor Analysis of Information Risk (FAIR) methodology. Present findings in language that executives and board members understand.
          </p>

          <ul class="mt-8 space-y-4">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="mt-1 inline-block h-2 w-2 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-cyan-400"></span>
              <div>
                <p class="font-medium text-slate-200">Monte Carlo Simulation</p>
                <p class="text-sm text-slate-400">10,000 iterations per risk scenario generating probability distributions for loss exposure, providing statistically robust estimates rather than single-point values.</p>
              </div>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="mt-1 inline-block h-2 w-2 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-cyan-400"></span>
              <div>
                <p class="font-medium text-slate-200">Dollar-Quantified ALE</p>
                <p class="text-sm text-slate-400">Annualized Loss Expectancy calculated for each finding, enabling cost-benefit analysis of remediation investments and risk transfer decisions.</p>
              </div>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="mt-1 inline-block h-2 w-2 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-cyan-400"></span>
              <div>
                <p class="font-medium text-slate-200">EPSS / KEV / CVSS Correlation</p>
                <p class="text-sm text-slate-400">Cross-references Exploit Prediction Scoring System (EPSS) probabilities, CISA Known Exploited Vulnerabilities (KEV) catalog, and CVSS scores to prioritize findings by real-world exploitability.</p>
              </div>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="mt-10 lg:mt-0">
          <div class="rounded-lg border border-navy-700 bg-navy-900 p-8">
            <h3 class="mb-4 text-lg font-semibold text-white">How It Works</h3>
            <ol class="space-y-4 text-sm text-slate-400">
              <li class="flex gap-3">
                <span class="flex h-6 w-6 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-cyan-600/20 text-xs font-bold text-cyan-400">1</span>
                <span>Scanners identify vulnerabilities with CVE, CVSS, and technical context</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex gap-3">
                <span class="flex h-6 w-6 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-cyan-600/20 text-xs font-bold text-cyan-400">2</span>
                <span>EPSS and KEV data overlay real-world exploit likelihood</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex gap-3">
                <span class="flex h-6 w-6 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-cyan-600/20 text-xs font-bold text-cyan-400">3</span>
                <span>FAIR model parameters are derived from finding context and asset criticality</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex gap-3">
                <span class="flex h-6 w-6 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-cyan-600/20 text-xs font-bold text-cyan-400">4</span>
                <span>Monte Carlo engine runs 10K simulations per scenario</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex gap-3">
                <span class="flex h-6 w-6 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-cyan-600/20 text-xs font-bold text-cyan-400">5</span>
                <span>Results presented as dollar-quantified ALE with confidence intervals</span>
              </li>
            </ol>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Deployment Flexibility -->
  <section class="bg-navy-900 py-16 sm:py-20">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white sm:text-4xl">Deployment Flexibility</h2>
        <p class="mt-4 max-w-3xl text-slate-400">
          Deploy the Donjon Platform however your environment requires. From a USB drive in an air-gapped facility to a CI/CD pipeline in the cloud, the platform adapts to your operational constraints.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 gap-6 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4">
        <div class="rounded-lg border border-navy-700 bg-navy-800 p-6 text-center">
          <div class="mx-auto mb-4 flex h-12 w-12 items-center justify-center rounded-lg bg-cyan-600/20">
            <svg class="h-6 w-6 text-cyan-400" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="1.5" stroke="currentColor" aria-hidden="true">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M3.75 3.75v4.5m0-4.5h4.5m-4.5 0L9 9M3.75 20.25v-4.5m0 4.5h4.5m-4.5 0L9 15M20.25 3.75h-4.5m4.5 0v4.5m0-4.5L15 9m5.25 11.25h-4.5m4.5 0v-4.5m0 4.5L15 15" />
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white">USB / Portable</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-400">Run directly from a USB drive. No installation required. Ideal for on-site assessments and restricted environments.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-lg border border-navy-700 bg-navy-800 p-6 text-center">
